Dow Jones's index dropped to almost seven percent. A similar volume drop was last recorded in 1987.
The index fell before it was announced, but as soon as it was shown that the assembly proposal did not go ahead, the index began to fall freely.
Congress withdraws: U.S. government can inject $700 billion into banking
