Armed fight: the MP3 Player against the mobile phone.
We advise you how to choose
While almost all mobile plays MP3 files, no MP3 player gets to make calls.
Which seems clear that it's better to just buy the phone.
Yet there are sufficient reasons for man to acquire only the reproducer.
The choice depends practically on the way of its use and the requirement of the future owner.
It will probably be difficult for him to acquire the most modern record player to hear Maxim Turbulenc's latest album on it.
On the other hand, this type of musical products such as LP records no longer come out, and as far as their quality is concerned, there is not a single objective reason to continue buying them.
If vinyl records with art rock, jazz, or blues are stacked on their shelves, you're probably dreaming, at least, of this kind of record player.
This is the same with the music that is on the way, i.e. the compressed, simplified music - the music in MP3.
And here there are price and quality categories.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend eight thousand crowns on a player, the same as for a Pink Floyd lover who will hardly taste the twenty-crown market helmets.
Two ends, between which there is enough space for each.
The choice is wide.
Also decides the battery life
Some of the best players get much more than just playing music and even what not even most mobiles do.
No current device is as universal as the phone.
In front of the most elementary functions such as phone, send messages, you can play music and video, record both, have a better or worse photography device and can even manage to navigate.
And when we take into consideration the Smartphone and the PDAs will also have in their pocket a small computer.
This is a small miracle since no fridge knows how to make a barbecue and no television can photograph.
The universality of mobiles also brings disadvantages.
The more functions you use on your mobile before the display indicator will be illuminated by asking to be recharged.
And the playing of music is one of the biggest energy gulps.
Few mobile phones are able to play music for more than ten or twelve hours, most of them much less.
In this sense, music players (especially the simplest players) clearly have a higher performance.
Therefore, keep in mind that cheap mobiles will not play more than two hours.
If in addition to this, on top of that, constantly call get still, for more safety, a loader for work - this is also valid for the most expensive appliances.
With the MP3 player this problem will not have it, because even the worst endure at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation after a load.
Another problem happens when recording music on your mobile phone.
Unfortunately only a part of the devices has the universal USB connector and, in addition, not all of them can connect directly to the computer without special software.
Of course it is possible to record music directly to the memory card but only in some unreduced reader drives can the small memory cards that are used on mobiles be connected.
In players, with some exception (iPod), no special software is required.
