In addition, meals were also included in the bill, while the restaurant has not been in operation for a long time.
The enthusiastic invoice makers also did not report that the travel agency chosen in Budapest exclusively organizes trips abroad, so that on the cash payment bill they foolishly indicated a journey within Hungary as service, which did not coincide with the agency's practice of issuing invoices.
Furthermore - as was known during the investigation - VAT was also included in the document, despite the fact that travel outside the territory of the European Union was exempt from taxes.
